children.name: Text Description
children.characters:
Checkboxes are used to enable binary choices. The user can have an individual 
choice or a collection of choices.

children.name: Text
children.characters:
Use a checkbox to present the user with a choice in a form.
A checkbox should be used to apply the users choice immediately, sometimes a user may have to select a save button to confirm their selection.

If you are intending to use in the case of enabling a feature, for example, use a toggle switch instead.

children.name: Text
children.characters: Checkboxes main default states are on or off.

children.name: Text
children.characters: Indeterminate state on a checkbox is neither on or off, it may be affected by another value that has been set affecting all checkboxes in a checkbox group, for example:

children.characters: When checkboxes are disabled, and a user hovers, the not-allowed cursor will show to offer the user more feedback that this checkbox is disabled

children.name: Text
children.characters: The focus state we use for this component is not currently available to use in Prism as a variable. But it is documented here and can be viewed in storybook.

children.name: Text
children.characters:
A user can tab through a Checkbox and select an item by clicking the enter key.
an outline will show around the current tabbed into element.
If a checkbox is on its own, an outline will show around the single checkbox - It its also paired with label text, the outline will show around the group.
